Haniel Pretax Profit Increases to $919.1 Million, FAS Reports

-- B y   E v a   v o n   S c h a p e r
-- 
2011-04-30T15:21:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/haniel-pretax-profit-increases-to-919-1-million-fas-reports.html
Franz Haniel & Cie GmbH saw 2010
pre-tax profit rise almost fourfold,  Frankfurter Allgemeine
Sonntagszeitung  reported, citing the compnay.  Earnings before taxes advanced to 620 million euros ($918
million) from 160 million euros a year earlier, while revenue
rose 12.5 percent to 27 billion euros, the newspaper said.  Sales were driven by  Metro AG (MEO) , the retailer in which Haniel
share a majority with the Schmidt-Ruthenbeck family, FAS said.  Haniel, which is owned by about 550 members of the Haniel
family, also controls  Europe â€™s biggest drug wholesaler  Celesio
